  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with significant legal consequences. Typically, penalties can include:\n\n1. Criminal Charges\n- Potential federal or state criminal prosecution\n- Imprisonment (often 10-20 years)\n- Substantial monetary fines\n\n2. Financial Penalties\n- Seizure of assets\n- Large financial penalties\n- Forfeiture of property obtained through illegal means\n\n3. Professional Consequences\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Potential business disqualification\n- Damage to professional reputation\n\n4. Additional Legal Risks\n- Civil litigation\n- International sanctions\n- Potential extradition in complex cases\n\nThese consequences can vary based on specific circumstances and jurisdiction. Consulting a legal professional would provide the most accurate information for a specific situation.",
